Class Enquiry

java.lang.Object
sc2002.bto.entity.Enquiry
public class Enquiry extends Object
Represents an enquiry submitted by an applicant regarding a BTO project. Tracks the enquiry status, messages, and responses.

  • Constructor Details

    • Enquiry

      public Enquiry(String enquiryId, Project project, Applicant applicant, String message)
      Creates a new enquiry with the specified details. The default status is set to PENDING.
      Parameters:
      enquiryId - Unique identifier for this enquiry
      project - The project this enquiry is about
      applicant - The applicant who submitted this enquiry
      message - The enquiry message content

    • setMessage

      public void setMessage(String message)
      Updates the enquiry message. Only allowed if the enquiry status is still PENDING.
      Parameters:
      message - The new message content

    • isEditableOrDeletable

      public boolean isEditableOrDeletable()
      Checks if the enquiry can be edited or deleted. An enquiry can only be edited or deleted if it has not been replied to yet.
      Returns:
      true if the enquiry can be edited or deleted, false otherwise

    • reply

      public void reply(String responseMessage)
      Adds a response to this enquiry and updates its status to REPLIED.
      Parameters:
      responseMessage - The response message to add

    • getEnquiryDetailsAsString

      A string containing all the enquiry details
